00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,000
to the end of the string?

276
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:10,000
It just reappears at the other end.

277
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,000
So it might fall off the end over here

278
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:17,000
and you pick it up over here.

279
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,000
And it just would continue to circulate

280
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:22,000
around and around the string.

281
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:30,000
That would be the picture of a right moving wave.

282
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:33,000
So that's a wave moving to the right.

283
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,500
And then there are waves

284
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:38,000
that can move to the left.

285
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,000
Left moving waves and right moving waves.

286
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:45,000
And both of them can exist on the string.

287
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,000
What about for the open string?

288
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:50,000
Were there left moving waves and right moving waves?

289
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,000
Yeah, you could imagine a left moving wave

290
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,000
and a right moving wave.

291
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,000
You start with a left moving wave.

292
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,500
But what happens when it gets

293
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,000
to the end in that case?

294
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,000
It gets reflected.

295
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,000
So in that case you

296
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,000
would have left going to right,

297
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,000
going to left, going to right.

298
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,000
The leftiness and the rightiness of it

299
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:07,000
would not be conserved in time.

300
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,000
The kind of things which are conserved in time

301
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,000
are the standing waves.

302
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:16,000
But for a closed string, there are running waves.

303
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:19,000
Go to the left and they go to the right.

304
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:25,000
Okay, let's talk about writing the...

305
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Oh, well, yeah, let's take particular kinds of waves now.

306
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:35,000
Particular kinds of waves would correspond to plain waves

307
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,000
moving up and down the string.

308
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Let's say right moving or left moving.

309
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:44,000
Now it's convenient to describe the waves

310
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:49,000
not by sines and cosines, but by exponentials.

311
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:58,000
Let's erase this over here.

312
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Exponentials are just linear, e to the i,

313
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:04,000
sigma, e to the i, n sigma.

314
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,000
Exponentials are just linear combinations

315
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:09,000
of sines and cosines.

316
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,000
In the case of the open string,

317
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:15,000
you are either restricted to sines or cosines

318
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
depending on whether it was Dirichlet

319
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:20,000
or Neumann boundary conditions.

320
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,500
For the closed strings, you

321
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:23,000
can have both sines and cosines,

322
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,000
but you can also have linear combinations

323
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,000
of sines and cosines.

324
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,000
So you can have exponential waves

325
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:32,000
propagating to the left or the right.

326
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:35,000
So the kind of waves that you can imagine

327
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,000
are e to the i, n sigma,

328
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,000
which would be, of course,

329
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:45,000
cosine sigma plus i, n...

330
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:53,000
cosine n sigma plus i sine n sigma.

331
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:57,000
We can choose to decompose things into exponentials.

332
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,000
In this way, if we like.

333
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:08,000
So let's do that.

334
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:13,000
Let's take x of sigma.

335
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,000
What we're going to do is exactly what we did

336
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,000
with the open string.

337
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:20,000
We're going to Fourier transform x of sigma.

338
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,000
But now the rule is neither Neumann or Dirichlet,

339
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:26,000
just that it comes back to itself

340
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,000
after going around by 2 pi.

341
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:31,000
The general form for the expansion of a function

342
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,000
which is periodic with a period 2 pi

343
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:37,000
is just, is a general form,

344
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,000
is that it's a sum

345
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,000
over all integers

346
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:46,000
of coefficients, let's call them xn,

347
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:51,000
times e to the i, n sigma.

348
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,000
n can be positive or negative.

349
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,000
If n is positive, think of

350
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
it as a right moving wave.

351
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:03,000
If n is negative, think of

352
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:06,000
it as a left moving wave.

353
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Okay, let's just check this.

354
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,000
Does this really have the property

355
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,000
that it comes back to itself

356
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:14,000
when sigma goes from 0 to 2 pi?

357
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,000
When sigma is 0,

358
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:19,000
e to the i, n sigma is 1.

359
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:22,000
What about when sigma is 2 pi?

360
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:25,000
e to the 2 pi is what?

361
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,000
e to the i times 2 pi is what?

362
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:33,000
How about e to the twice 2 pi i?

363
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,000
Okay.

364
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,000
Right.

365
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,000
So every one of these,

366
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,000
supposing I were to put over here,

367
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:41,000
instead of n, I were to put n over 2,

368
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,000
a half.

369
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:47,000
Does it come back to itself after a cycle?

370
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,000
No.

371
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,000
So it's necessary to put integers here.

372
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,000
And this is the most general form

373
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:58,000
of a periodic function when it's Fourier expanded

374
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:01,000
on a line between 0 and 2 pi,

375
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,000
assuming that it's periodic.

376
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
We're going to write this as,

377
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,000
I'm going to write it

378
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,000
as a sum of two terms.

379
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,000
Well, a sum of three terms.

380
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:16,000
The first terms are n for positive n.

381
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,000
Alright, this is going to be

382
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,000
a sum of n greater than 0.

383
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:23,000
Those correspond to the right moving waves,

384
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,000
which go around to the right.

385
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,000
Now I want to write the left moving waves,

386
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,000
which I could write the same way,

387
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,000
except let n be negative,

388
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,500
or I could write it as

389
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:36,000
a sum of n greater than 0,

390
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:40,500
but let's call it x minus n

391
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:45,000
e to the minus i n sigma.

392
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:48,000
e to the i sigmas with positive coefficients here

393
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:51,000
correspond to right moving waves,

394
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,000
with a negative coefficient that corresponds

395
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,000
to left moving waves.

396
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,000
That's beautiful.

397
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,000
Thank you.

398
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,000
By moving, don't you have to have time coordinates?

399
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,000
Yes, it's a sigma and plus,

400
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,000
sigma and plus, right, yes.

401
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,000
Yes.

402
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:15,000
The time coordinate is usually in here,

403
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:18,000
e to the plus i, e to the minus i.

404
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,000
Alright, so think of these in any cases,

405
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:23,000
left moving waves and right moving waves.

406
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,000
Something's missing here.

407
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,000
x zero.

408
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,000
n equals 0.

409
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,000
Alright, so let's put that back in.

410
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:34,000
And what is that?

411
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,000
You know what that is?

412
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,000
x zero.

413
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,000
It's x zero, but what's the physics of it?

414
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,000
What's the physical meaning of it?

415
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:43,000
Physics.

416
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,000
Center of gravity.

417
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,000
Center of mass.

418
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,000
Center of mass of the string.

419
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,000
The actual location of the string.

420
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:54,000
The center of the string.

421
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,000
x zero.

422
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:59,000
Same thing for y.

423
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,000
Exactly the same thing for y.

424
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,000
I think I will not write it.

425
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,000
But y of sigma is equal

426
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,000
to the same kind of sum,

427
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:10,000
y sub n, e to the i n sigma,

428
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,500
y of minus n, e

429
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:13,000
to the minus i n sigma.

430
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:19,000
So you can have waves which correspond to

431
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:22,000
fluctuations along the x axis,

432
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:25,000
waves which correspond to fluctuations along the y axis.

433
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,000
They go around the string.

434
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:30,000
And this is the general form.

435
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
What do you do with this?

436
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:35,000
You take the Lagrangian for the string,

437
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,000
which I haven't written down,

438
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,000
but it's exactly the same Lagrangian

439
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:41,000
as for the open string.

440
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,000
Exactly the same.

441
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,000
The string is still imagined to be made up of

442
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,000
little mass points with strings and balls.

443
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,000
You write the Lagrangian of the string,

444
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,000
exactly as before.

445
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,000
The only difference is you integrate now

446
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:56,000
from zero to two pi.

447
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:59,000
d sigma.

448
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Same thing as before.

449
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:05,000
The x by d tau squared, tau is time,

450
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:10,000
minus the x by d sigma squared.

451
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Exactly what we wrote earlier.

452
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,000
And we do the same thing for y.

453
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,000
Plus, plus,

454
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:21,000
minus, minus, minus, plus,

455
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:28,000
y terms of exactly the same kind.

456
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:32,000
So we have now a decomposition of x

457
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:35,000
into discrete Fourier modes.

458
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:41,000
We have a Lagrangian.

459
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,000
What are the time-dependent things in x of sigma?

460
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,000
They're the x-ends.

461
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,000
The x-ends are sort of coordinates

462
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:49,250
Each oscillation has a shape, but

463
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:51,500
it also has a time dependence,

464
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:54,000
and the time dependence is buried

465
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,500
